question.p:
Question 6 of 479: Biochemistry

 Describe DNA replication. ...  Origin of replication: continuous DNA synthesis on leading strand and discontinuous (Okazaki fragments) on lagging strand. Primase makes an RNA primer on which DNA polymerase can initiate replication. DNA polymerase reaches primer of preceding fragment; 5'-->3' exonuclease activity of DNA polymerase I degrades RNA primer; DNA ligase seals;
3'-->5' exonuclease activity of DNA polymerase 'proofreads' each added nucleotide. DNA topoisomerases create a nick in the helix to relieve supercoils
